| `TestStorageProfileSnapshotClassHonored` | `test_vm_restore_succeeds_with_storage_profile_snapshot_class` | VM restore succeeds and VM is running/SSH-accessible after restore from snapshot created with StorageProfile snapshotClass |
| `TestStorageProfileSnapshotClassFallback` | `test_vm_snapshot_falls_back_to_driver_based_selection` | VolumeSnapshot uses driver-matched VolumeSnapshotClass when StorageProfile has no snapshotClass |

**Key design decisions:**
- `ResourceEditor` context manager for temporary StorageProfile modification (auto-reverts)
- Fixture dependency chain ensures StorageProfile is patched BEFORE snapshot creation
- Function-scoped VM/snapshot fixtures for full test isolation
- Uses `VirtualMachineClusterInstancetype`/`VirtualMachineClusterPreference` matching existing `rhel_vm_for_snapshot` pattern
- GRAVEYARD compliance: no absolute file paths, no `time.sleep`, verifies actual cluster state
